<paragraphs
xml:id="lines-secant-lines-and-rates-of-change">
<title>Lines, secant lines, and rates of
change</title>

<p> When talking about the average rate of change of
a measurement we compute the ratio of change in output over change in
input (often time). This ratio is also the slope of a line that we call
the secant line.
</p>

<p> The secant line connects two points that lie on
the graph of a function. We call one of the points the <term>base
point</term>.
</p>

<p> <em>When we pick our two points on a graph, we
are still computing the slope of a line through these points (even
though it has a new name – the secant line).<!-- linebreak --></em>
</p>

